This paper is primarily focused on image inpainting, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks and dilated convolutions also suggests that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The preservation of fine-grained spatial information could also make it relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
